    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hmm, you do have sort of a valid point in that the whitelist admins will usually not sign messages manually, though I wonder how that server would look like. In any case, any automated service that signs messages for an account should be extremely well guarded - not only could the whitelist be tampered with, but funds could be stolen, tokens exchanged, etc.\r\n\r\nAll in all, I think this requirement is too specific to be part of OpenZeppelin, specially considering we provide the tools for users to implement these custom features on their own. You could either use `Ownable` or create a new role to reset the whitelist, and have your crowdsale also extend from `PausableCrowdsale`, thereby allowing pausers to stop the crowdsale process until the issue has been dealt with.",
